<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 93 / Observer: Flight control
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
While coming to accept that his luggage may go missing when he flies, a
reader is perturbed that British Airways' general sense of direction has
gone awry.
In its current 'dream ticket' promotion, the airline claims that 'two
flights on Club World to New York could give you and your partner the chance
to stroll through the Arab bazaars of Casablanca'.
