<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 93 / Mubarak reappoints premier
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARK NICHOLSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CAIRO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
EGYPT's President Hosni Mubarak began his third term of office yesterday by
retaining Mr Atef Sidki, his 63-year-old prime minister, who in turn
announced the first moves in a long-awaited cabinet reshuffle.
Mr Mubarak promised during his inauguration speech on Tuesday that 'new
blood' would follow his endorsement in last week's referendum for a further
six years as Egypt's head of state. He has been hinting at cabinet changes
since April and last month spoke of possible 'unlimited changes' in the
government.
However, his first move was to reappoint Mr Sidki, a man who embodies Mr
Mubarak's preference for stability and cautious reform. Mr Sidki, who
formally appoints Egypt's cabinet, then announced that Mr Mohammed Salheddin
Hamid was to be replaced as governor of the central bank by Mr Ismail
Hassan, chairman of the Bank of Alexandria.
